This skill summarises and points to authoritative third-party material
about the Dutch Referentie GrootboekSchema (RGS) and Standard Business
Reporting (SBR), including publications by:

- The RGS standard owner / Taakgroep RGS (referentiegrootboekschema.nl)
- SBR Nederland and Logius (sbr-nl.nl, logius.nl, nltaxonomie.nl)
- De Belastingdienst, the Kamer van Koophandel (KvK), CBS, SBR Nexus,
  SBR Wonen, and the AFM
- Onderzoeksbureau GBNED / Gerard Bottemanne (boekhoudplaza.nl,
  softwarepakketten.nl), cited as the de-facto practitioner reference
- Bookkeeping-software vendors (MoneyBird, Exact, Twinfield, AFAS,
  e-Boekhouden, SnelStart, Yuki, Asperion) for product-specific behaviour

Those documents, schemas, taxonomies, and product names remain the
property of their respective publishers and are referenced under fair-use
principles for interoperability and education. RGS reference codes and the
RGS taxonomy are published by the RGS standard owner; this skill does not
redistribute the official RGS master file — download it from
referentiegrootboekschema.nl.

Versions and rule numbers were verified at the time of writing. Always
verify the operative version of any cited rule, code, or taxonomy against
the publisher's primary source before relying on it for a regulated
filing.
